<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="281" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1230,2011]" pageId="5" pageNumber="281">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1518,1543]" pageId="5" pageNumber="281">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Pleurae without a dark strip below postpronotum and wing base (
<figureCitation box="[1081,1166,1518,1543]" captionStart="FIGURES 14–17" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1984,2007]" captionTargetBox="[167,1404,469,1964]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1435,425,1964]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 14–17. Hirtodrosophila nungara sp. nov., holotype, ♂. 14. Habitus, lateral view; 15. Thorax, dorsal view; 16. Head, frontal view; 17. Head, latero-frontal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2594978/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="281">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
). Epandrium with large setae in ventral lobe and surstylus with 5 peg-like prensisetae and a crescent process dorsal to prensisetae (
<figureCitation box="[1340,1423,1554,1579]" captionStart="FIGURES 18–23" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1934,1957]" captionTargetBox="[240,1340,222,1909]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[208,1383,193,1924]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 18–23. Hirtodrosophila nungara sp. nov., male terminalia, holotype. 18. Epandrium, cerci and surstyli, posterior view; 19. Hypandrium and gonopods, posterior view; 20. Surstyli and decasternum, ventral view; 21–23. Aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme and paraphyses, ventral, dorsal and right lateral views, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2594980/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="281">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
). Aedeagus arrow-shaped with tip membranous and bearing two subapical lateral spurs, with three overlapping bends apically (
<figureCitation box="[327,465,1626,1651]" captionStart="FIGURES 18–23" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1934,1957]" captionTargetBox="[240,1340,222,1909]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[208,1383,193,1924]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 18–23. Hirtodrosophila nungara sp. nov., male terminalia, holotype. 18. Epandrium, cerci and surstyli, posterior view; 19. Hypandrium and gonopods, posterior view; 20. Surstyli and decasternum, ventral view; 21–23. Aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme and paraphyses, ventral, dorsal and right lateral views, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2594980/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="281">Figs. 21–23</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="8" lastPageNumber="284" pageId="5" pageNumber="281" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1230,2011]" pageId="5" pageNumber="281">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,1662,1687]" pageId="5" pageNumber="281">Description</emphasis>
. 
<specimenCount box="[354,378,1663,1686]" pageId="5" pageNumber="281" type="male">♂</specimenCount>
. Head (
<figureCitation box="[468,607,1662,1687]" captionStart="FIGURES 14–17" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1984,2007]" captionTargetBox="[167,1404,469,1964]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1435,425,1964]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 14–17. Hirtodrosophila nungara sp. nov., holotype, ♂. 14. Habitus, lateral view; 15. Thorax, dorsal view; 16. Head, frontal view; 17. Head, latero-frontal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2594978/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="281">Figs. 16–17</figureCitation>
). Yellow. Frons and face yellow, fronto-orbital plates indistinct with the same color of the frons (as in 
<taxonomicName authority="Junges &amp; Robe &amp; Gottschalk, 2019" authorityName="Junges &amp; Robe &amp; Gottschalk" authorityYear="2019" box="[480,616,1699,1723]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Hirtodrosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="281" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rondonia" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[480,616,1699,1723]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="281">H. rondonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[622,711,1698,1723]" pageId="5" pageNumber="281">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[622,711,1698,1723]" pageId="5" pageNumber="281" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
). Length ratio of mid to anterior orbital setae = 0.42 (0.33–0.50), length ratio of mid to posterior orbital setae = 0.44 (0.33–0.56), vt index = 1.20, ocellar triangle yellowish about 35% (26–46%) of frontal length. Facial carina not prominent, with the same color of the frons. Antennae yellowish with flagellomeres slightly grey, aristae with 4–5 dorsal and one ventral branches, plus terminal fork. Palpus yellowish with an apical seta and two or three smaller preapical setae. Red eyes with short piles. Genae yellow, first genal setae about 17% (16–18%) of the vibrissae length. Cheek index = 0.20 (0.15–0.24), eye index = 1.13 (1.11– 1.16).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,1230,2011]" lastBlockId="6.[151,1437,151,391]" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="282" pageId="5" pageNumber="281">
Thorax (
<figureCitation box="[294,420,1950,1975]" captionStart="FIGURES 14–17" captionStartId="6.[151,264,1984,2007]" captionTargetBox="[167,1404,469,1964]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[151,1435,425,1964]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURES 14–17. Hirtodrosophila nungara sp. nov., holotype, ♂. 14. Habitus, lateral view; 15. Thorax, dorsal view; 16. Head, frontal view; 17. Head, latero-frontal view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2594978/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="281">Fig. 14–15</figureCitation>
). Yellow. Length = 0.65 (0.60–0.68) mm, width = 0.51 (0.50–0.53) mm, 6 irregular rows of acrostichals, no prescutellar setae. Dc index = 0.44 (0.44–0.44). Scutellum yellow. Basal scutellar setae convergent. Scut position index = 0.73 (0.70–0.80). Two prominent katepisternal setae and a row of setulae between them. Anterior katepisternal about 51% (38–60%) of the length of posterior one. Pleurae and legs yellow.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,391]" pageId="6" pageNumber="282">
Wings (
<figureCitation box="[287,372,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 44–47" captionStartId="14.[151,264,1962,1985]" captionTargetBox="[183,1382,1239,1849]" captionTargetId="figure@14.[151,1436,1210,1902]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURES 44–47. Wings. 44. H. rondonia sp. nov., holotype, ♂; 45. H. nungara sp. nov., holotype, ♂; 46. H. jukyry sp. nov., holotype, ♂; 47. H. crioula sp. nov., holotype, ♂." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2594990/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="282">Fig. 45</figureCitation>
). Yellow with veins dark yellow. Length = 1.25 (1.04–1.37) mm. Length to width ratio = 0.63 (0.60–0.67). Indices: C = 1.52 (1.33–1.75); 
<date box="[639,667,260,284]" pageId="6" pageNumber="282">4v</date>
= 1.67 (1.50–1.92); 
<date box="[897,925,260,285]" pageId="6" pageNumber="282">5x</date>
= 2.52 (2.00–3.00); 4c = 1.26 (1.12–1.38); M = 0.63 (0.56–0.72); hb = 2.02 (1.80–2.28); prox. x = 0.41 (0.37–0.46).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,151,391]" pageId="6" pageNumber="282">Abdomen. Main color yellow. Tergites II–V with fainted brown posterior marginal bands not reaching lateral area.</paragraph>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2594978/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="282" startId="6.[151,264,1984,2007]" targetBox="[167,1404,469,1964]" targetPageId="6">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1984,2038]" pageId="6" pageNumber="282">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,343,1984,2007]" pageId="6" pageNumber="282">FIGURES 14–17.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Junges &amp; Robe &amp; Gottschalk, 2019" authorityName="Junges &amp; Robe &amp; Gottschalk" authorityYear="2019" box="[352,612,1985,2007]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Hirtodrosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="282" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nungara" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[352,612,1985,2007]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="282">Hirtodrosophila nungara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[621,705,1985,2006]" pageId="6" pageNumber="282">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[621,705,1985,2006]" pageId="6" pageNumber="282" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, holotype, ♂. 14. Habitus, lateral view; 15. Thorax, dorsal view; 16. Head, frontal view; 17. Head, latero-frontal view.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<caption httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2594980/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="283" startId="7.[151,264,1934,1957]" targetBox="[240,1340,222,1909]" targetPageId="7">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1934,2018]" pageId="7" pageNumber="283">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,341,1934,1957]" pageId="7" pageNumber="283">FIGURES 18–23.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Junges &amp; Robe &amp; Gottschalk, 2019" authorityName="Junges &amp; Robe &amp; Gottschalk" authorityYear="2019" box="[349,606,1935,1957]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Hirtodrosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="283" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nungara" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[349,606,1935,1957]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="283">Hirtodrosophila nungara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[614,697,1935,1956]" pageId="7" pageNumber="283">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[614,697,1935,1956]" pageId="7" pageNumber="283" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, male terminalia, holotype. 18. Epandrium, cerci and surstyli, posterior view; 19. Hypandrium and gonopods, posterior view; 20. Surstyli and decasternum, ventral view; 21–23. Aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme and paraphyses, ventral, dorsal and right lateral views, respectively.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,151,716]" box="[199,611,151,176]" pageId="8" pageNumber="284">Body length = 1.38 (1.27–1.52) mm.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,151,716]" pageId="8" pageNumber="284">
Terminalia (
<figureCitation box="[339,480,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 18–23" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1934,1957]" captionTargetBox="[240,1340,222,1909]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[208,1383,193,1924]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 18–23. Hirtodrosophila nungara sp. nov., male terminalia, holotype. 18. Epandrium, cerci and surstyli, posterior view; 19. Hypandrium and gonopods, posterior view; 20. Surstyli and decasternum, ventral view; 21–23. Aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme and paraphyses, ventral, dorsal and right lateral views, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2594980/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="284">Figs. 18–23</figureCitation>
). Epandrium microtrichose, with four upper and 14 lower setae, 11 of lower ones located on ventral lobe (
<figureCitation box="[420,502,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURES 18–23" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1934,1957]" captionTargetBox="[240,1340,222,1909]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[208,1383,193,1924]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 18–23. Hirtodrosophila nungara sp. nov., male terminalia, holotype. 18. Epandrium, cerci and surstyli, posterior view; 19. Hypandrium and gonopods, posterior view; 20. Surstyli and decasternum, ventral view; 21–23. Aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme and paraphyses, ventral, dorsal and right lateral views, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2594980/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="284">Fig. 18</figureCitation>
). Cerci microtrichoses, not fused with epandrium. Surstylus not microtrichose, with 5 peg-like prensisetae, two smaller setulae following prensisetae row, about 10 inner and no outer setae. Surstyli not covered by ventral lobe of epandrium. Decasternum broad (
<figureCitation box="[893,980,295,320]" captionStart="FIGURES 18–23" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1934,1957]" captionTargetBox="[240,1340,222,1909]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[208,1383,193,1924]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 18–23. Hirtodrosophila nungara sp. nov., male terminalia, holotype. 18. Epandrium, cerci and surstyli, posterior view; 19. Hypandrium and gonopods, posterior view; 20. Surstyli and decasternum, ventral view; 21–23. Aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme and paraphyses, ventral, dorsal and right lateral views, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2594980/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="284">Fig. 20</figureCitation>
). Hypandrium with the anterior margin wider than in 
<taxonomicName authority="Junges &amp; Robe &amp; Gottschalk, 2019" authorityName="Junges &amp; Robe &amp; Gottschalk" authorityYear="2019" box="[307,598,332,356]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Hirtodrosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="284" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rondonia" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[307,598,332,356]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="284">Hirtodrosophila rondonia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[605,695,332,357]" pageId="8" pageNumber="284">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[605,695,332,357]" pageId="8" pageNumber="284" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, gonopods fused with hypandrium, each bearing a seta near outer margin (
<figureCitation box="[247,333,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURES 18–23" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1934,1957]" captionTargetBox="[240,1340,222,1909]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[208,1383,193,1924]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 18–23. Hirtodrosophila nungara sp. nov., male terminalia, holotype. 18. Epandrium, cerci and surstyli, posterior view; 19. Hypandrium and gonopods, posterior view; 20. Surstyli and decasternum, ventral view; 21–23. Aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme and paraphyses, ventral, dorsal and right lateral views, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2594980/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="284">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
). Paraphysis with 5 upper and 3 median small setulae on inner margin. Aedeagus arrow-shaped with a membranous tip, subapical portion convex in lateral view. Lateral outwards spurs (as in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Burla" authorityYear="1956" box="[1237,1368,404,428]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Hirtodrosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="284" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="subgilva">
<emphasis box="[1237,1368,404,428]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="284">H. subgilva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) with three small overlapping bends (
<figureCitation box="[503,630,439,464]" captionStart="FIGURES 18–23" captionStartId="7.[151,264,1934,1957]" captionTargetBox="[240,1340,222,1909]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[208,1383,193,1924]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 18–23. Hirtodrosophila nungara sp. nov., male terminalia, holotype. 18. Epandrium, cerci and surstyli, posterior view; 19. Hypandrium and gonopods, posterior view; 20. Surstyli and decasternum, ventral view; 21–23. Aedeagus, aedeagal apodeme and paraphyses, ventral, dorsal and right lateral views, respectively." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2594980/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="284">Fig. 21–23</figureCitation>
). Aedeagal apodeme fused with and shorter than aedeagus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,151,716]" box="[199,352,476,501]" pageId="8" pageNumber="284">
<specimenCount box="[199,221,477,500]" pageId="8" pageNumber="284" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
. Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="284" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,151,716]" pageId="8" pageNumber="284">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,511,536]" pageId="8" pageNumber="284">Etymology.</emphasis>
The name “nungara” means “similar” in the Tupi-Guarani language and it is an allusion to its similarity with 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Burla" baseAuthorityYear="1956" box="[322,412,548,572]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Hirtodrosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="284" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gilva">
<emphasis box="[322,412,548,572]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="284">H. gilva</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1436,151,716]" pageId="8" pageNumber="284">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,501,583,608]" pageId="8" pageNumber="284">Geographic distribution.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authority="Junges &amp; Robe &amp; Gottschalk, 2019" authorityName="Junges &amp; Robe &amp; Gottschalk" authorityYear="2019" box="[513,802,584,608]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Hirtodrosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="284" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nungara" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[513,802,584,608]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="284">Hirtodrosophila nungara</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[815,911,583,608]" pageId="8" pageNumber="284">
